<subSubSection id="A6465046E96E9D9A22EA0652D2F6D303" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D5083E55F2D9EEADDA31CA1F7E7E86CA" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9F1D9626D68EA96358E75F00E4F08BE1" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">
The new species 
<taxonomicName id="ADCDF6FC84B5C94AD1760572ABD35EFB" authorityName="S. Jin Zeng, Y. C. Xu &amp; D. F. Cui" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Memecylaceae" genus="Tigridiopalma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tigridiopalma exalata" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exalata">
<emphasis id="3C561DA9F85A48E2E1799FF54696CF89" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Tigridiopalma exalata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="D6E3701596ADBB46CCA83F31D5B04D78" genus="T." lsidName="T. magnifica" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" rank="species" species="magnifica">
<emphasis id="224A6096C56B798A1CCB1242EC43970F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">T. magnifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a short stem, huge basal leaves, scorpioid cymes, and 5-merous flowers, but differs in its ribbed and densely pale yellow puberulent petioles, connectives of longer stamens with a distinct dorsal short spur at their base, and wingless capsules.
</paragraph>
<caption id="6B572646B47BFC32A0A23276886BC97D" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.176.63619.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/531679" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
