<subSubSection id="3F5EB0FD8C187C59DCE511E596C9F8B9" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" type="preliminary conservation assessment">
<paragraph id="EA2B3637E2C99D71B04CE736BD04EDA8" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Preliminary conservation assessment.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AFC7D3E74A014CEB0E1A0700C1D54CD0" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">
About 1000 mature 
<taxonomicName id="3B76263D0E5659DA09058CAC243381D2" authorityName="S. Jin Zeng, Y. C. Xu &amp; D. F. Cui" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Memecylaceae" genus="Tigridiopalma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tigridiopalma exalata" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exalata">
<emphasis id="5A05A65E6F3C2ADF591D675557C47F73" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Tigridiopalma exalata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
individuals from one locality have been found in less than 60 km2 up to now. This area can be classified as the extent of occurrence. The plants are not well protected in a Forest Park and the populations are severely fragmented. This species has horticultural potential as an ornamental plant. According to the IUCN Standards and Petitions Committee (2019), a category of Endangered (EN) is recommended for 
<taxonomicName id="BA6B2E6747414A76945376DFD18A6EF9" authorityName="S. Jin Zeng, Y. C. Xu &amp; D. F. Cui" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Memecylaceae" genus="Tigridiopalma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Tigridiopalma exalata" order="Myrtales" pageId="0" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exalata">
<emphasis id="3793B6CC6D7C83BE3F1AA6BEB8E0E6BA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="33">Tigridiopalma exalata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the present.
</paragraph>
